item.title: Peejay Who Once Was Minsma add a quote by Arthur Koestler
item.description: "In my youth I regarded the Universe as an open book, printed in the language of physical equations, whereas now it appears to me as a text written in invisible ink, of which, in our rare moments of grace, we are able to decipher a small fragment." -- Arthur Koestler

item.title: Peejay Who Once Was Minsma add a quote by Oscar Wilde
